Iâ€™m not quite sure how to put into words the fight with kindred. Particularly when trynd slashes through lambâ€™s bow. Obviously trynd cannot kill lamb because kindred is a primordial entity, arguably the strongest of any of them (the others being things like fiddlesticks the entity of fear) she is literally a god. But the moment she â€œdodgesâ€ is unnatural. Itâ€™s almost as though the world bent for a moment to ensure tryndâ€™s blade wouldnâ€™t touch lamb. His sword slows down, lamb moves in a fraction of a second with no real effort and then simply tilts her head.

Itâ€™s also an incredible visual to see what a struggle on the verge of death is like. Wolfâ€™s relentless assault and lambâ€™s arrows combined very quickly remind you that from a lore perspective kindred is the absolute last thing you want to tango with

The new trailer however went in completely the opposite direction, it had very respectful masculine vibes, like a more polished, more tasteful (which I feel bad saying because it was an iconic cult classic and a masterpiece for its time) version of something like the OG Heavy Metal the movie, as well as a nod to old fashioned Samurai movies, OG Berserk, historical Valkyries, etc. Itâ€™s been a long time since common media has shown something masculine in a respectable, tasteful way and it almost brought a tear to my eye like it touched a part of my soul.
